KW  - COVID-19 pandemic
KW  - Limited investor attention
KW  - Market reaction
KW  - Negativity bias
KW  - News release
AB  - We find that the COVID-19 pandemic increases (decreases) stock return sensitivity to market-wide (firm-specific) news, which is associated with return reversals (delayed reactions). These results are consistent with limited investor attention and investors paying heightened (reduced) attention to macro (micro) information after the outbreak. There are more biased reactions when the epidemic spread is higher, to good news than bad news, for firms headquartered in pandemic epicenters, and for larger stocks. We also find higher (lower) imbalanced trading, information flow, and price efficiency associated with market-wide (firm-specific) news during the pandemic.
